flowchart LR
  F0["F0 Source Intake<br/>Receives the raw paper and all attached material without judging too early."]
  F1["F1 Source Resolution<br/>Separates facts, claims, conflicts, guesses, and decisions so agents know what is real."]
  F2["F2 Product SOT<br/>Creates the product source of truth that every later agent must obey."]
  F3["F3 Understanding Alignment<br/>Asks only questions that change product, risk, architecture, execution, or authority."]
  F4["F4 Architecture Candidate<br/>Turns the SOT into a system design with constraints, tradeoffs, and boundaries."]
  F5["F5 Product Face<br/>Defines screens, states, wallet flows, mobile, a11y, performance, and visual evidence."]
  F6["F6 Specialist Reviews<br/>Security, cyber, Solana, frontend, backend, QA, DevOps, and architecture critique the plan."]
  F7["F7 Onchain Package<br/>For Solana/Quasar: accounts, ABI, PDA, CPI, compute units, authorities, and Auditor scope."]
  F8["F8 Security Scan Plan<br/>Defines scan timing, scope, owner, tools, acceptance rules, and blocking policy."]
  F9["F9 Human Architecture Gate<br/>A human approves, rejects, or sends architecture back before decomposition."]
  F10["F10 Documentation OS<br/>Turns approved architecture into specs, decisions, contracts, diagrams, and evidence paths."]
  F11["F11 Decomposition<br/>Creates gated Hermes cards with owner, executor, reviewer, risk, surfaces, and done contract."]
  F12["F12 Execution<br/>Agents execute bounded work without expanding their authority."]
  F13["F13 Verification<br/>Runs tests, scans, screenshots, Auditor checks, and domain-specific validation."]
  F14["F14 Independent Review<br/>A different reviewer validates the work, evidence, and Receipt Five."]
  F15["F15 Human R3/R4 Gate<br/>High-risk work needs explicit human risk ownership, waiver control, and rollback ownership."]
  F16["F16 Promotion<br/>Promotes only when evidence, review, security, rollback, monitoring, and human gates are ready."]
  F17["F17 Production Monitoring<br/>Watches runtime health, product behavior, security signals, and release safety."]
  F18["F18 Learning Loop<br/>Converts pilot evidence into Factory VNext instead of relying on opinion."]
  V36["VNext / Factory V3.6<br/>Removes what was heavy, tightens what was vague, and updates contracts after real use."]

  F0 --> F1 --> F2 --> F3 --> F4 --> F5 --> F6 --> F7 --> F8 --> F9 --> F10 --> F11 --> F12 --> F13 --> F14 --> F15 --> F16 --> F17 --> F18 --> V36

  subgraph W["Critical Worker Lane<br/>Specialists receive explicit packets instead of vague instructions."]
    WPF["Product Face Validator<br/>Checks visible product quality: screens, states, mobile, wallet UI, a11y, and screenshots."]
    WAUD["Solana/Quasar Auditor Runner<br/>Uses the Auditor path for accounts, PDA, CPI, compute, authorities, and Quasar-specific risk."]
    WSEC["Codex Security Runner<br/>Runs security/cyber checks at the declared timing and writes scan evidence."]
    WREV["Independent Reviewer<br/>Prevents self-approval by reviewing the work with a different identity."]
    WHUM["Human Gate Clerk<br/>Records real human architecture, R3/R4, and promotion decisions without faking approval."]
  end

  F5 --> WPF
  F7 --> WAUD
  F8 --> WSEC
  F13 --> WPF
  F13 --> WAUD
  F13 --> WSEC
  F14 --> WREV
  F9 --> WHUM
  F15 --> WHUM
  F16 --> WHUM

  subgraph R["Hermes Runtime Lane<br/>The factory floor that turns methodology into enforceable movement."]
    R0["factoryctl gate-report<br/>Preflights the card and tells Hermes which workers are required."]
    R1["Worker Packets<br/>Machine-readable requests with trigger, inputs, output field, and blocking policy."]
    R2["Hermes Ready Gate<br/>Blocks weak cards before agents start execution."]
    R3["Hermes Done Gate<br/>Blocks completion when Receipt Five or required evidence is missing."]
    R4["Receipt Five<br/>Captures changed work, artifacts, verification, reviewer result, next action, and transition event."]
    R5["Exit-Code Enforcement<br/>Blocked transitions return non-zero so scripts cannot treat failure as success."]
  end

  F11 --> R0 --> R1 --> R2 --> F12
  F13 --> R3 --> R4 --> F14
  R2 --> R5
  R3 --> R5

  subgraph G["Hard Gates<br/>These are stricter than normal project management ceremonies."]
    G1["Product Face Gate<br/>Visible product surfaces need Product Face Packet before ready and product_face_result before done."]
    G2["Auditor Gate<br/>Solana/Quasar work needs onchain package and Auditor evidence or explicit human waiver."]
    G3["Security Gate<br/>R3/R4 and sensitive surfaces need Codex Security/Cybersecurity evidence."]
    G4["Anti-Self-Review Gate<br/>Executor and reviewer identities must be different."]
    G5["R3/R4 Human Gate<br/>R3/R4 need human_gate_packet; R4 additionally needs r4_gate."]
  end

  WPF --> G1
  WAUD --> G2
  WSEC --> G3
  WREV --> G4
  WHUM --> G5

  G1 --> R2
  G2 --> R2
  G3 --> R3
  G4 --> R3
  G5 --> F15
